po di Studio Endocrinologia e Malattie del Metabolismo SIPMeL","target":"Gruppo di Studio Endocrinologia e Malattie del Metabolismo SIPMeL","line":47},{"title":"Diagnostica di Laboratorio delle Malattie del Surrene","target":"Diagnostica di Laboratorio delle Malattie del Surrene","line":57},{"title":"Intervalli di Riferimento e Limiti Decisionali","target":"Intervalli di Riferimento e Limiti Decisionali","line":57},{"title":"ISO 15189","target":"ISO 15189","line":57}],"metadata":{"type":"source","title":"SIPMeL - Diagnostica di Laboratorio dell'Insufficienza Surrenalica Primaria","created":"2026-06-13","updated":"2026-06-13","tags":["#laboratorio-medico","#source","#sipmel","#endocrinologia","#surrene"],"status":"developing","address":"c-000100","source_type":"guideline","authors":["Federica D'Aurizio","Renato Tozzoli","Romolo M. Dorizzi","Vincenzo Brescia","Antonio Fortunato","Ottavia Porzio","Marina Vitillo","Gruppo di Studio Endocrinologia e Malattie del Metabolismo (GdS-EMM) - SIPMeL"],"publication":"La Rivista Italiana della Medicina di Laboratorio / Italian Journal of Laboratory Medicine","file":".raw/unlocked_SIPMEL - La diagnostica di laboratorio delle malattie del surrene. Raccomandazioni pratiche per l'insufficienza surrenalica primaria.pdf","related":["[[SIPMeL]]","[[Gruppo di Studio Endocrinologia e Malattie del Metabolismo SIPMeL]]","[[Diagnostica di Laboratorio delle Malattie del Surrene]]","[[Intervalli di Riferimento e Limiti Decisionali]]","[[SIPMeL - Diagnostica di Laboratorio del Feocromocitoma e Paraganglioma]]","[[SIPMeL - Diagnostica di Laboratorio della Sindrome di Cushing]]","[[ISO 15189]]"],"key_claims":["Il test combinato basale (cortisolo sierico totale CST, oppure indice di cortisolo libero ICL, oppure cortisolo salivare del mattino CSM, associati alla misura dell'ACTH plasmatico) rappresenta il test di ingresso per la diagnosi di insufficienza surrenalica primaria (ISP) (raccomandazione 1, grado 1).","Un valore di CST < 140 nmol/L (50 microg/L), o di ICL < 12, o di CSM < 4,1 nmol/L (1,5 microg/L), associato a un valore di ACTH superiore a 2 volte il limite superiore dell'intervallo di riferimento metodo-dipendente, è fortemente indicativo di ISP (raccomandazione 4, grado 1).","La conferma diagnostica di ISP richiede il test dinamico da stimolo con corticotropina (ACTH test / test al Synacthen) a dose standard: valori di CST inferiori a 500 nmol/L (180 microg/L) a 30 o 60 minuti dalla somministrazione di 250 microg di ACTH sintetico sono diagnostici per ISP (raccomandazione 5, grado 1); al momento non esistono cut-off validati per ICL o CSM dopo stimolo.","Un valore elevato di renina attiva (PRC) associato a livelli di aldosterone (PAC) basso-normali (in genere <100 pmol/L) suggerisce l'esecuzione del test combinato basale (raccomandazione 2, grado 2): la renina è spesso il primo indicatore ormonale a modificarsi nelle forme primarie di insufficienza surrenalica.","Un valore basso di DHEAS (< 2,0 micromol/L o 0,74 microg/mL) suggerisce l'esecuzione del test combinato basale (raccomandazione 3, grado 2), poiché nell'ISP la riduzione di DHEA/DHEAS precede la caduta degli steroidi glicoattivi.","L'eziologia autoimmune (distruzione della corticale surrenalica mediata da autoanticorpi, tra cui gli anti-21-idrossilasi) è oggi responsabile dell'82% dei casi di ISP (morbo di Addison), seguita da forme infettive (9%, storicamente la tubercolosi era la causa principale) e altre cause (9%).","Il cortisolo sierico totale (CST) è fortemente condizionato dai livelli di transcortina (CBG) e albumina: in condizioni di alterazione di queste proteine di trasporto (cirrosi, sindrome nefrosica, uso di estro-progestinici, gravidanza) è preferibile l'indice di cortisolo libero (ICL = CST/CBG) o, dove disponibile, il cortisolo libero sierico.","Il cortisolo libero urinario (CLU) NON è raccomandato come test di screening per l'insufficienza surrenalica, poiché a basse concentrazioni la misura non fornisce informazioni diagnostiche utili e presenta numerose criticità preanalitiche e analitiche."]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[]},"smart_blocks:Wiki/sources/SIPMeL - Diagnostica di Laboratorio dell'Insufficienza Surrenalica Primaria.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"w9pk3m","at":1781675972352},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.0580041,0.02847573,0.01221505,0.07662052,0.04546281,-0.0839288,-0.04185665,0.06919683,-0.01700978,-0.01490898,-0.02533091,-0.08482872,-0.01010454,0.05421476,0.01813582,-0.00406039,-0.00181799,0.03668582,0.03369788,-0.05504308,0.14469627,-0.03963576,-0.02919555,-0.0663329,0.05785545,0.09222737,0.00934823,0.00652765,-0.07418673,-0.18617754,0.0004638,0.01805618,0.03135509,-0.04826181,0.02990604,0.00724105,0.03184947,0.04168152,0.03541654,0.06521124,0.0309044,0.05487868,-0.00524593,0.02161564,-0.00262604,-0.03641715,-0.03026987,0.02771012,0.00214316,-0.03679654,-0.06516898,0.05238092,-0.01050704,0.04778607,-0.00092087,0.01180284,0.05297884,-0.01668441,0.03228651,0.02830498,0.01987845,0.05667868,-0.24079044,0.02550185,0.03430486,0.03323155,-0.07531539,0.00865021,-0.00841033,-0.01222294,0.00894973,-0.06933615,0.01003793,0.03302931,0.01277671,-0.0312302,0.00074184,0.00114011,-0.00361592,0.01161499,0.00117468,0.05756817,-0.0022976,0.00589088,0.01600487,-0.0246028,0.00566085,0.00368087,0.03481296,-0.03886002,-0.05414788,-0.0595304,0.04221101,0.06085022,-0.02465369,0.00619984,-0.0515666,0.04029204,-0.00669888,0.08523969,0.00231613,-0.02837721,0.00252012,-0.0272729,-0.01646446,0.03737707,-0.01899013,-0.03276881,-0.01371404,0.03876641,0.0087998,-0.01930855,0.08955383,-0.03998628,-0.03597926,-0.01430037,0.06222626,-0.00353807,-0.04918348,0.07554755,0.04519552,0.01255847,0.06351265,-0.03334648,0.02195069,-0.00887305,0.0053295,0.05491206,0.04750061,0.03285201,0.07134113,0.06310078,-0.07229033,0.01825294,0.00365737,-0.0044623,0.04998136,-0.01385802,0.0177559,-0.0115582,-0.00458987,-0.1283371,-0.04261175,-0.06670206,-0.102576